It honestly feels a bit bad to even write this review; the game's really cute for what little it is, and it's just 49 cents.  But still... I feel that I at least owe as much to the community.

This game has:
 - Nice graphics, if obviously taken from a generic game graphics pack somewhere (and what's with the super-unfitting stuff like the bloody spikes and sawblades?);
 - Original and very cute character sprites;
 - Very pleasant music, if only two songs that very abruptly shift back and forth when you die;
 - Extremely simple but by no means horrible gameplay;
 - A cute pug.

This game does not have:
 - Any, and I mean even the tiniest, most miniscule inkling of depth, or reason to play whatsoever beyond the point of taking 5 seconds to see how cute your character's sprite and its run animation is.  There are no upgrades, no unlocks (except a rabbit avatar apparetly??), no obvious goal, no real options, no modes, no anything.  You, as a pug, automatically run and manually jump past basic obstacles made with generic, if decently used, graphical assets and collect pug head icons that add to a meaningless score.  that is it.  that is literally all there is to it.

It's cute, but not worth buying, not even for 49 cents.  There are many far better games in this style that you can play completely free in your browser all over the internet.  Could've been neat for a free app to show the dev's chops for making something cute and simple maybe, at most, but selling it for any price was silly.  Might have been worth it if it came with the two-song soundtrack though, I really liked those songs.

Welp, I just spent nearly twice as long writing this review as I did playing the game.  Time to go give myself a pat on the back, and buy a pug.
